    {"id": "univ190", "text": "UNIV 190 The Clarkson Seminar. Credits: 3. Prerequisites: first-year standing. Description: Interdisciplinary seminar exploring connections between technology, society, and culture. Required for ALL Clarkson undergraduate students regardless of major. Typically taken in the fall semester of the first year. Offered every fall.", "metadata": {"category": "course", "dept": "UNIV", "level": "100"}},
    {"id": "fy100", "text": "FY100 First-Year Seminar. Credits: 1. Prerequisites: first-year standing. Description: Orientation to university life, academic skills, campus resources, and community engagement. Required for all first-year undergraduate students. Taken alongside UNIV 190 in the first fall semester.", "metadata": {"category": "course", "dept": "FY", "level": "100"}},

    # ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
